those things are not

00:36:06.600 --> 00:36:08.350 align:middle line:84%
going to the classes
or the lectures.

00:36:08.350 --> 00:36:09.150 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: No.

00:36:09.150 --> 00:36:12.960 align:middle line:84%
>>MOORJANI: So the message
is not landing on the ones

00:36:12.960 --> 00:36:14.325 align:middle line:90%
that it's targeted at.

00:36:14.325 --> 00:36:17.160 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It's actually
reinforcing the ones

00:36:17.160 --> 00:36:19.410 align:middle line:84%
that you're speaking of,
the ones who are already

00:36:19.410 --> 00:36:22.350 align:middle line:84%
tend to go into more
self-service and narcissism.

00:36:22.350 --> 00:36:23.430 align:middle line:90%
It's like that's OK.

00:36:23.430 --> 00:36:23.850 align:middle line:90%
You go.

00:36:23.850 --> 00:36:24.690 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: Yes.

00:36:24.690 --> 00:36:26.850 align:middle line:84%
So what ends up
happening is that we've

00:36:26.850 --> 00:36:30.974 align:middle line:84%
created a world where the
ones who are already repressed

00:36:30.974 --> 00:36:32.016 align:middle line:90%
repress themselves more--

00:36:32.016 --> 00:36:33.099 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Even more, yeah.

00:36:33.099 --> 00:36:35.670 align:middle line:84%
>>MOORJANI: But those
are the voices we need.

00:36:35.670 --> 00:36:38.340 align:middle line:84%
We need the empaths
and the kind people

00:36:38.340 --> 00:36:41.670 align:middle line:84%
and the service-oriented
people to have big egos

00:36:41.670 --> 00:36:43.350 align:middle line:90%
because what does the ego do?

00:36:43.350 --> 00:36:46.450 align:middle line:90%
It magnifies who you are.

00:36:46.450 --> 00:36:49.800 align:middle line:84%
So if you are a narcissist,
you don't want a narcissist

00:36:49.800 --> 00:36:51.240 align:middle line:90%
with a big ego.

00:36:51.240 --> 00:36:54.480 align:middle line:84%
But if you have an empath,
you do want an empath

00:36:54.480 --> 00:36:57.730 align:middle line:84%
to have a healthy
ego so they can share

00:36:57.730 --> 00:36:58.885 align:middle line:90%
their gifts with the world.

00:36:58.885 --> 00:37:01.060 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So you say
that, right now, we're

00:37:01.060 --> 00:37:03.545 align:middle line:84%
having more and more people
incarnate who are empaths?

00:37:03.545 --> 00:37:04.345 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: Yes.

00:37:04.345 --> 00:37:06.700 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Because this is
the trajectory that's going

00:37:06.700 --> 00:37:07.995 align:middle line:90%
to heal the world ultimately?

00:37:07.995 --> 00:37:08.490 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: Yes.

00:37:08.490 --> 00:37:10.448 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So let's talk
about that and the work

00:37:10.448 --> 00:37:12.820 align:middle line:84%
that you're bringing
forward in your new book,

00:37:12.820 --> 00:37:15.310 align:middle line:84%
and then we can talk about
what is the ultimate goal.

00:37:15.310 --> 00:37:19.480 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it seems to me the
church of nature and friendship

00:37:19.480 --> 00:37:23.495 align:middle line:84%
and laughter is really the
church we want to attend.

00:37:23.495 --> 00:37:24.295 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: Yes.

00:37:24.295 --> 00:37:27.580 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And kindness and,
like you've said, friendship.

00:37:27.580 --> 00:37:29.170 align:middle line:84%
So let's talk
about your new book

00:37:29.170 --> 00:37:32.260 align:middle line:84%
and what you're trying
to impart through it.

00:37:32.260 --> 00:37:36.250 align:middle line:84%
>>MOORJANI: So
basically what I would

00:37:36.250 --> 00:37:40.540 align:middle line:84%
like people to know is that
we've all forgotten how to be

00:37:40.540 --> 00:37:42.790 align:middle line:90%
kind and how to be empathic.

00:37:42.790 --> 00:37:45.970 align:middle line:84%
We've become very
fear-based, and fear

00:37:45.970 --> 00:37:47.530 align:middle line:90%
makes us very divisive.

00:37:47.530 --> 00:37:49.990 align:middle line:84%
And the reason why
fear makes us divisive

00:37:49.990 --> 00:37:52.910 align:middle line:84%
is fear puts us into
a survival mode,

00:37:52.910 --> 00:37:54.610 align:middle line:84%
and when you're
in survival mode,

00:37:54.610 --> 00:37:57.020 align:middle line:84%
it's every person
for themselves.

00:37:57.020 --> 00:37:59.200 align:middle line:84%
And so it makes
us very divisive.

00:37:59.200 --> 00:38:04.130 align:middle line:84%
And most of our mainstream
systems of any kind,

00:38:04.130 --> 00:38:07.210 align:middle line:84%
whether it's an education
system, a medical system,

00:38:07.210 --> 00:38:10.810 align:middle line:84%
mainstream media, and
so on, their messages

00:38:10.810 --> 00:38:12.220 align:middle line:90%
are very fear-based.

00:38:12.220 --> 00:38:15.500 align:middle line:84%
And I don't think they're doing
it consciously, maybe they are,

00:38:15.500 --> 00:38:17.750 align:middle line:84%
but I'm going to give them
the benefit of the doubt.

00:38:17.750 --> 00:38:22.220 align:middle line:84%
It could be well-meaning
to take action quickly.

00:38:22.220 --> 00:38:24.730 align:middle line:84%
And so in order to get people
to take action quickly,

00:38:24.730 --> 00:38:27.280 align:middle line:84%
we send them very
fear-based messages.

00:38:27.280 --> 00:38:30.770 align:middle line:84%
That if you don't do this
now, this will happen to you.

00:38:30.770 --> 00:38:31.570 align:middle line:90%
And so--

00:38:31.570 --> 00:38:34.450 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I think also in the
age of scientific materialism,

00:38:34.450 --> 00:38:37.850 align:middle line:84%
to be a cynic is to
be a wise person.

00:38:37.850 --> 00:38:40.420 align:middle line:84%
So you're already
going to put yourself

00:38:40.420 --> 00:38:41.984 align:middle line:84%
in the mode of
rejecting anything

00:38:41.984 --> 00:38:43.067 align:middle line:90%
that's outside of the box.

00:38:43.067 --> 00:38:44.720 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: 100%.

00:38:44.720 --> 00:38:46.915 align:middle line:84%
And this is something that
I have a problem with--

00:38:46.915 --> 00:38:47.715 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Me too.

00:38:47.715 --> 00:38:49.720 align:middle line:84%
>>MOORJANI: --is that
anybody who actually

00:38:49.720 --> 00:38:52.570 align:middle line:84%
sees through the
fear and who actually

00:38:52.570 --> 00:38:56.770 align:middle line:84%
sees what is driving the
problem in the first place,

00:38:56.770 --> 00:38:58.690 align:middle line:84%
it's actually the fear
of all these things

00:38:58.690 --> 00:39:00.800 align:middle line:84%
that's creating the
problem that they

00:39:00.800 --> 00:39:02.050 align:middle line:90%
think they're trying to solve.

00:39:02.050 --> 00:39:04.120 align:middle line:84%
But when you see
through the fear,

00:39:04.120 --> 00:39:08.050 align:middle line:84%
you're actually labeled as
delusional or woo-woo or any

00:39:08.050 --> 00:39:09.170 align:middle line:90%
of those things.

00:39:09.170 --> 00:39:12.410 align:middle line:84%
And that's something that
even I've dealt with.

00:39:12.410 --> 00:39:13.210 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh, yeah.

00:39:13.210 --> 00:39:15.250 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: Yeah.

00:39:15.250 --> 00:39:17.950 align:middle line:84%
But I would rather
think the way I

00:39:17.950 --> 00:39:22.390 align:middle line:84%
do because I get to live
my life from a space of joy

00:39:22.390 --> 00:39:27.130 align:middle line:84%
than to actually fall into
that fear-based living, which

00:39:27.130 --> 00:39:29.220 align:middle line:84%
is what gave me cancer
in the first place.

00:39:29.220 --> 00:39:30.100 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Absolutely.

00:39:30.100 --> 00:39:34.360 align:middle line:84%
And so, like you say, from
educational systems down,

00:39:34.360 --> 00:39:38.470 align:middle line:84%
it is popular in the
scientific materialist way

00:39:38.470 --> 00:39:41.320 align:middle line:84%
to be critical of everything,
to critique and be critical.

00:39:41.320 --> 00:39:44.287 align:middle line:84%
And when you see
any headlines-- it

00:39:44.287 --> 00:39:45.620 align:middle line:90%
doesn't matter what publication.

00:39:45.620 --> 00:39:48.260 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't matter which service
anywhere around the world.

00:39:48.260 --> 00:39:50.590 align:middle line:84%
--it's all going to be of a
critical nature bringing up

00:39:50.590 --> 00:39:52.840 align:middle line:90%
the worst in humanity.

00:39:52.840 --> 00:39:58.150 align:middle line:84%
And people confuse that with
being a critical thinker,

00:39:58.150 --> 00:40:00.575 align:middle line:84%
and this couldn't
be more opposite.

00:40:00.575 --> 00:40:01.375 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: 100%.

00:40:01.375 --> 00:40:04.330 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Could you please
expand on that for us?

00:40:04.330 --> 00:40:08.305 align:middle line:84%
To be critical is not
to be critically aware.

00:40:08.305 --> 00:40:12.280 align:middle line:84%
>>MOORJANI: Yes,
so we have taken

00:40:12.280 --> 00:40:16.040 align:middle line:84%
being critical to an extreme
where we have become debunkers.

00:40:16.040 --> 00:40:16.840 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:40:16.840 --> 00:40:18.136 align:middle line:84%
>>MOORJANI: And that's
what I have a problem--

00:40:18.136 --> 00:40:19.810 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It doesn't matter
what side you're on of anything.

00:40:19.810 --> 00:40:22.340 align:middle line:84%
We're all debunkers if
you're buying into what's

00:40:22.340 --> 00:40:23.590 align:middle line:90%
being put before us right now.

00:40:23.590 --> 00:40:24.850 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: Exactly.

00:40:24.850 --> 00:40:27.070 align:middle line:84%
And we have really
become debunkers,

00:40:27.070 --> 00:40:32.380 align:middle line:84%
and what we have forgotten--
so people are so determined

00:40:32.380 --> 00:40:36.490 align:middle line:84%
to be right that they've
forgotten to be kind.

00:40:36.490 --> 00:40:37.430 align:middle line:90%
And so when--

00:40:37.430 --> 00:40:38.185 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh, boy, yes.

00:40:38.185 --> 00:40:38.985 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: Yeah.

00:40:38.985 --> 00:40:43.180 align:middle line:84%
And so when you have situations
like whatever has been going on

00:40:43.180 --> 00:40:47.461 align:middle line:84%
on this planet for
the last few years,

00:40:47.461 --> 00:40:50.980 align:middle line:84%
what people have forgotten
is that it doesn't matter

00:40:50.980 --> 00:40:54.220 align:middle line:84%
what side you're on
and which side is right

00:40:54.220 --> 00:40:56.210 align:middle line:90%
or which side is wrong.

00:40:56.210 --> 00:40:59.180 align:middle line:84%
What actually is
causing the problem

00:40:59.180 --> 00:41:02.480 align:middle line:84%
is how we're dividing
ourselves and how

00:41:02.480 --> 00:41:03.655 align:middle line:90%
we're hating each other.

00:41:03.655 --> 00:41:04.613 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh, boy, yes.

00:41:04.613 --> 00:41:07.250 align:middle line:84%
>>MOORJANI: That is at the
root of this whole problem,

00:41:07.250 --> 00:41:09.620 align:middle line:90%
not who is right, who is wrong.

00:41:09.620 --> 00:41:11.120 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Absolutely.

00:41:11.120 --> 00:41:14.120 align:middle line:84%
And it's really
clouding the field.

00:41:14.120 --> 00:41:14.920 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: Yes.

00:41:14.920 --> 00:41:17.060 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: The
emotional field which

00:41:17.060 --> 00:41:18.950 align:middle line:84%
interfaces with Earth's
emotional field,

00:41:18.950 --> 00:41:21.990 align:middle line:84%
the mental plane,
which is all connected.

00:41:21.990 --> 00:41:23.600 align:middle line:84%
We're all connected
with one another

00:41:23.600 --> 00:41:28.430 align:middle line:84%
into this horrid cloud of
confusion and separation

00:41:28.430 --> 00:41:29.690 align:middle line:90%
and anxiety and fear.

00:41:29.690 --> 00:41:31.160 align:middle line:90%
That's what's ruling right now.

00:41:31.160 --> 00:41:31.325 align:middle line:90%
Period.

00:41:31.325 --> 00:41:33.080 align:middle line:84%
>>MOORJANI: That
is what's ruling.

00:41:33.080 --> 00:41:36.420 align:middle line:84%
And when we die, we find
out that we're actually

00:41:36.420 --> 00:41:37.220 align:middle line:90%
all connected.

00:41:37.220 --> 00:41:38.720 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yeah,
we're all connected.

00:41:38.720 --> 00:41:40.310 align:middle line:90%
You found that out the hard way.

00:41:40.310 --> 00:41:41.690 align:middle line:90%
Joyful but hard way.

00:41:41.690 --> 00:41:43.940 align:middle line:84%
I was interviewing an
astrologer yesterday,

00:41:43.940 --> 00:41:46.490 align:middle line:84%
and we were talking
about this cloudiness

00:41:46.490 --> 00:41:48.800 align:middle line:84%
in the field and
the nature of it,

00:41:48.800 --> 00:41:50.450 align:middle line:90%
the fear-based nature of it.

00:41:50.450 --> 00:41:55.460 align:middle line:84%
And she was saying that as the
larger Pluto movement happens,

00:41:55.460 --> 00:41:57.540 align:middle line:90%
it's moving into Aquarius, OK?

00:41:57.540 --> 00:41:59.460 align:middle line:84%
When it moves into
Aquarius, it's

00:41:59.460 --> 00:42:03.000 align:middle line:84%
a very permeable thought
field and can be easily

00:42:03.000 --> 00:42:04.140 align:middle line:90%
swayed and influenced.

00:42:04.140 --> 00:42:06.510 align:middle line:84%
So it's as though we're
ramping up to that,

00:42:06.510 --> 00:42:10.240 align:middle line:84%
and technology is taking
us there even faster.

00:42:10.240 --> 00:42:14.490 align:middle line:84%
So now the awareness of
that kind of fluidity

00:42:14.490 --> 00:42:17.100 align:middle line:84%
of the mental
field, I think, it's

00:42:17.100 --> 00:42:20.220 align:middle line:84%
upon us now to take
responsibility and start

00:42:20.220 --> 00:42:23.250 align:middle line:84%
feeding it good
nutrients, good thoughts,

00:42:23.250 --> 00:42:26.850 align:middle line:84%
good nutrients, feeding
it emotions that are,

00:42:26.850 --> 00:42:28.930 align:middle line:90%
like you say, kind and helpful.

00:42:28.930 --> 00:42:30.690 align:middle line:84%
So talk about that
a little bit and how

00:42:30.690 --> 00:42:34.530 align:middle line:84%
you recommend to people through
your work and your book they

00:42:34.530 --> 00:42:36.960 align:middle line:84%
reestablish healthy
self-esteem and can

00:42:36.960 --> 00:42:40.440 align:middle line:84%
start creating a cohesive
field of emotion and thought.

00:42:40.440 --> 00:42:42.870 align:middle line:84%
>>MOORJANI: I love that, and
I love the way you think.

00:42:42.870 --> 00:42:46.770 align:middle line:84%
So what I actually feel
is that, right now,

00:42:46.770 --> 00:42:51.150 align:middle line:84%
because of materialistic
science and the beliefs

00:42:51.150 --> 00:42:54.030 align:middle line:84%
of the world today is
that we are so focused

00:42:54.030 --> 00:43:01.140 align:middle line:84%
on science and technology and
AI that our souls are actually

00:43:01.140 --> 00:43:02.970 align:middle line:90%
hungry, very hungry.

00:43:02.970 --> 00:43:05.700 align:middle line:84%
Our consciousness-- let's
say our consciousness is

00:43:05.700 --> 00:43:06.870 align:middle line:90%
deprived and hungry.

00:43:06.870 --> 00:43:09.840 align:middle line:84%
We're feeding our brain
but not our heart.

00:43:09.840 --> 00:43:13.960 align:middle line:84%
So what's happening is we have
developed all this technology,

00:43:13.960 --> 00:43:18.240 align:middle line:90%
but we are immature.

00:43:18.240 --> 00:43:20.430 align:middle line:90%
We're consciously unaware.

00:43:20.430 --> 00:43:24.240 align:middle line:84%
So currently, all this
technology that we've developed

00:43:24.240 --> 00:43:27.760 align:middle line:84%
is being used for negative
and not for positive.

00:43:27.760 --> 00:43:30.570 align:middle line:84%
In other words, we
have more technology

00:43:30.570 --> 00:43:33.280 align:middle line:84%
that could kill the planet
than could feed the planet.

00:43:33.280 --> 00:43:34.155 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Absolutely.

00:43:34.155 --> 00:43:35.550 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: Why is that?

00:43:35.550 --> 00:43:38.190 align:middle line:84%
And that in itself
tells us a lot

00:43:38.190 --> 00:43:42.420 align:middle line:84%
about where we are in our
conscious awareness evolution.

00:43:42.420 --> 00:43:44.560 align:middle line:90%
We have a long way to go.

00:43:44.560 --> 00:43:46.860 align:middle line:84%
So what we really
need to start doing,

00:43:46.860 --> 00:43:49.200 align:middle line:84%
and this is what I
try to do, and this

00:43:49.200 --> 00:43:52.170 align:middle line:84%
is what I hope my work
contributes in doing

00:43:52.170 --> 00:43:56.040 align:middle line:84%
and everything I put out,
everything that I put out

00:43:56.040 --> 00:44:00.730 align:middle line:84%
in my name, I want it to
raise conscious awareness.

00:44:00.730 --> 00:44:03.960 align:middle line:84%
Not just raise joy that's
important and kindness and

00:44:03.960 --> 00:44:06.660 align:middle line:84%
empathy, but all of
those things even

00:44:06.660 --> 00:44:09.100 align:middle line:90%
they raise conscious awareness.

00:44:09.100 --> 00:44:12.580 align:middle line:84%
And when we come from a
place of kindness and joy,

00:44:12.580 --> 00:44:15.210 align:middle line:84%
and when we teach people
that it's possible,

00:44:15.210 --> 00:44:17.479 align:middle line:84%
and when we teach people
that that's actually

00:44:17.479 --> 00:44:19.812 align:middle line:84%
all that matters when you
die, that's all that matters--

00:44:19.812 --> 00:44:20.880 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That's
all that matters,

00:44:20.880 --> 00:44:22.935 align:middle line:84%
and that's a choice every
moment of every day.

00:44:22.935 --> 00:44:24.630 align:middle line:90%
>>MOORJANI: Yes, yes.

00:44:24.630 --> 00:44:28.140 align:middle line:84%
And when that can be seen
as the strength, when

00:44:28.140 --> 00:44:31.260 align:middle line:84%
instead of seeing ruthlessness
as a strength-- you see,

00:44:31.260 --> 00:44:34.080 align:middle line:84%
that's the other problem,
is that we look up

00:44:34.080 --> 00:44:35.400 align:middle line:90%
to ruthless people.

00:44:35.400 --> 00:44:38.370 align:middle line:84%
We vote them in to
positions of power.

00:44:38.370 --> 00:44:42.630 align:middle line:84%
We need to vote in people who
are kind, who are empathic.

00:44:42.630 --> 00:44:45.390 align:middle line:84%
So when we start to
see those and when

00:44:45.390 --> 00:44:49.260 align:middle line:84%
we start to redefine what
the word strength means,

00:44:49.260 --> 00:44:50.850 align:middle line:90%
and we redefine it--

00:44:50.850 --> 00:44:54.150 align:middle line:84%
because at the moment, we
see empathy and sensitivity

00:44:54.150 --> 00:44:55.230 align:middle line:90%
as a weakness.

00:44:55.230 --> 00:44:57.960 align:middle line:84%
What if we decided
it was a strength?

00:44:57.960 --> 00:45:00.900 align:middle line:84%
And that people who were
willing to be vulnerable

00:45:00.900 --> 00:45:05.700 align:middle line:84%
and to show their sensitivity
and we saw them as strong?

00:45:05.700 --> 00:45:07.170 align:middle line:90%
That would shift.

00:45:07.170 --> 00:45:08.220 align:middle line:90%
It would soon shift.

00:45:08.220 --> 00:45:11.740 align:middle line:84%
Once we bring all that
into the education system

00:45:11.740 --> 00:45:14.190 align:middle line:84%
